From: David Howells <dhowells@redhat.com>
Date: Wed, 31 May 2023 12:04:22 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] kcm: Convert kcm_sendpage() to use MSG_SPLICE_PAGES
Git-commit: 5bb3a5cb3e217b838e85661f527818e16ce61bec
Patch-mainline: v6.5-rc1
References: bsc#1216396

Convert kcm_sendpage() to use sendmsg() with MSG_SPLICE_PAGES rather than
directly splicing in the pages itself.

This allows ->sendpage() to be replaced by something that can handle
multiple multipage folios in a single transaction.

Signed-off-by: David Howells <dhowells@redhat.com>
cc: Tom Herbert <tom@herbertland.com>
cc: Tom Herbert <tom@quantonium.net>
